### Learning From Each Other's Journeys: Case Studies from Open Communities - 31 July

![Alt: Hand-drawn image by scriberia is on the right of the digital poster: three people are sitting around a fire whose flames form the words ‚ÄúThe Fireside Chat‚Äù. They are holding speech bubbles on sticks in lieu of marshmallows.](https://assets.buttondown.email/images/ff3f4451-ca9f-4888-bd97-1982c718485a.png?w=960&fit=max)

Thank you so much to [Aleksandra Nenadic](https://www.linkedin.com/in/aleksandra-nenadic-bb64b96/)(The Carpentries), [Chris Holdgraf](https://www.linkedin.com/in/chrisholdgraf/)<span style="color: rgb(72, 83, 101)">(2i2c/Jupyter),</span> and [Yanina Bellini Saibene](https://www.linkedin.com/in/yabellini/)(RLadies+), for sharing their expertise on governance from their own open communities. This session was chaired by [Arielle Bennet](https://www.linkedin.com/in/ariellebennett/) and [Yo Yehudi](https://www.linkedin.com/in/yoyehudi/). Thanks to Sara Villa for providing support with online facilitation.

> *Words matter, but you can also have a name that is empty. We want to take actions to put meaning and value to our name. (Yanina Bellini Saibene)*

