## Overview of Talks and Workshops: July 2025

**Sara Villa, Emma Karoune, Aman Goel and Malvika Sharan** spoke at the STEP-UP conference on 7th July:

- **Sara** gave a talk about [Contextualising open science training programmes](https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.15830238), presenting her work leading Open NeuroSeeds (OLS‚Äôs Open Seeds contextualised to neuroscience)

![Sara presenting in a stand a slide on a big projector with a slide saying Let's work together, questions? ideas?](https://assets.buttondown.email/images/6c2e65b6-23b3-4c23-8881-55503682a69f.png?w=960&fit=max)

- **Emma‚Äôs** talked focused on [Professionalising diverse data science roles](https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.15812514), an essential focus in the current research landscape.
  
  ![Picture of Emma Karoune from Step Up conference where she spoke about current research technical landscape](https://assets.buttondown.email/images/ad141d19-d0ff-45fd-881e-21d995a49f78.png?w=960&fit=max)
  
- **Aman** delivered a passionate talk about [Diversity and Inclusion in Practice](https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.15827837).
  
  ![](https://assets.buttondown.email/images/c77bcbdf-f7f6-408b-8963-fcf8ade2df78.png?w=960&fit=max)
  
- **Malvika** gave a keynote on [Shaping Research (culture) through Communities Lessons from Open Science.](https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.15825320)

![Picture of Malvika from Step Up. She is standing in front of the lecture theater with red chairs next to her.](https://assets.buttondown.email/images/38b70721-de37-43be-b428-2322b6ea1607.png?w=960&fit=max)

- **Malvika Sharan** delivered the keynote at SciPy 2025, [The Myth of Artificial - Spotlighting Community Intelligence for Responsible Science](https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.15851499), where she talked about how open science initiatives like Open Life Science (OLS), *The Turing Way*, and others demonstrate how these communities provide the foundational infrastructure for science to serve society responsibly. Find some pictures on [SciPy Linkedin page](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/scipy-conference_scipy2025-activity-7348831488747978753-Brvy).

> *If you are in a room, there is a reason why you‚Äôre there. Don‚Äôt be afraid to share your own perspective.* (Malvika Sharan)

 

*As always, you can find an ongoing record of all of our work in our* [*Zenodo Community*](https://zenodo.org/communities/the-turing-way/) *page.*

